article.headline: Holy Cross 68, Boston U. 49
article.story: BOSTON -- Andrew Beinert scored a career-high 18 points to lead Holy Cross to its first road victory this season, a 68-49 rout of Boston University on Friday night. Andrew Keister added career highs of 15 points and 11 rebounds for the Crusaders (5-9, 1-6 on the road). Holy Cross led wire-to-wire and broke the game open with a 16-2 run early in the second half to hand BU (5-7) its fourth straight loss. The Crusaders beat the Terriers for the sixth straight time and lead the series, 50-12. BU suffered its eighth straight regular season loss at Agganis Arena. Beinert, entering the game 14-for-35 from 3-point range, was 4-for-5 Friday night. Colin Cunningham added 13 points and R.J. Evans 12 for the Crusaders. Jake O?Brien led BU with 16 points. Scoring leader Corey Lowe had a season-low 4 points and was ejected in the second half for his second technical foul.
